    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-28T12:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-28T12:36:00-05:00" n="1084"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1084">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/3920.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-28T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have just received following from Brazilian Minister: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Have taken necessary steps subject your cable this day and those sent
                            through British Legation by Admiral Craddock. Minister Foreign Affairs
                            with full agreement Minister of War has cabled most complete orders for
                            release persons stated by same cables as in prison or persecuted
                            Cordoba, Guanajuato. May add that up to present moment Mexican
                            Government have shown themselves quite willing to comply with my
                            request.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Minister</hi>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
